jasmine.clock().install();
// put whatever valid arg you want, you can even use just 0 as the ctor arg.
var baseTime = new Date(2013, 9, 23);
jasmine.clock().mockDate(baseTime);

// an example fo if you wanted time to elapse, but not compulsory when using
jasmine.clock().tick(50)
expect(new Date().getTime()).toEqual(baseTime.getTime() + 50);


afterEach(function () {
    jasmine.clock().uninstall();
});

As per: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/26152796/mock-date-constructor-with-jasmine


To see in action, I used this when testing the "should dispatch AuthenticateSuccess action" auth.effect in the recipe-book project
